ENTRY       EC 2.5.1.107                Enzyme
NAME        verruculogen prenyltransferase;
            FtmPT3
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups;
            Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups (only sub-subclass identified to date)
SYSNAME     dimethylallyl-diphosphate:verruculogen dimethylallyl-O-transferase
REACTION    dimethylallyl diphosphate + verruculogen = diphosphate + fumitremorgin A [RN:R10341]
ALL_REAC    R10341
SUBSTRATE   dimethylallyl diphosphate [CPD:C00235];
            verruculogen [CPD:C20045]
PRODUCT     diphosphate [CPD:C00013];
            fumitremorgin A [CPD:C20564]
COMMENT     Found in a number of fungi. Catalyses the last step in the biosynthetic pathway of the indole alkaloid fumitremorgin A. The enzyme from the fungus Neosartorya fischeri is also active with fumitremorgin B and 12alpha,13alpha-dihydroxyfumitremorgin C.
